---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Home">
  <section class="hero">
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="Tales From the Age of Men" class="hero-logo" />
    <p class="subtitle">A Lord of the Rings Total Conversion Mod for Bannerlord</p>
    <p class="tagline">
      Experience Middle-earth in Mount &amp; Blade II: Bannerlord. Command the armies of Gondor, Rohan, Erebor,
      Mordor, and more across 16 factions with hundreds of unique troops, lords, and equipment.
    </p>
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center;">
      <a href="/download" class="btn btn-primary">Download</a>
      <a href="/troops" class="btn btn-secondary">Browse Troops</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>16 Factions</h3>
        <p>From the realms of Gondor and Rohan to the dark forces of Mordor and Isengard. Each faction features unique cultures, troops, and equipment.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Hundreds of Troops</h3>
        <p>Custom troop trees for every faction with unique skills, equipment, and upgrade paths. Dwarven legionaries, Elven archers, Uruk-hai berserkers, and more.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Custom Lords & Heroes</h3>
        <p>380+ lords and 415+ heroes with custom skills, traits, biographies, and appearances inspired by Tolkien's world.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Custom Equipment</h3>
        <p>Faction-specific armor, weapons, and mounts. Dwarven plate, Elven mail, Gondorian steel, and Orcish crude iron.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Custom Map</h3>
        <p>A sprawling Middle-earth map with 658 settlements across all regions, from the Shire to Mordor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Active Development</h3>
        <p>Built for Bannerlord v1.3. Regular updates with new content, balance changes, and features.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
